    "FeDeRA [101] uses a simpler initialization method.",
    "It directly applies SVD to pre-trained weights to initialize LoRA.",
    "Retaining the principal components of the pre-trained weights aligns the direction and magnitude of weight updates across different clients to handle data heterogeneity.",
    "Additionally, FFA-LoRA [102] freezes one low-rank matrix and fine-tunes only the other.",
    "This reduces inconsistency during server aggregation of LoRA gradients, alleviating the optimization instability caused by non-IID data."
